  "task": "Given the embedded packet (metric map and four records) compute for each record: priority_value = metric1 * metric2 - 0.6 * metric3 + metric4. Rank records by priority_value descending but escalate any record that breaches the hard threshold rule first. Mark any record that is contradictory or under-supported as needs_review. Run a sensitivity check by shifting node_shift_um by +/-sensitivity_shift_pct and report how ranks and escalation status change. Produce two deliverables: (1) connectome_registration_audit.xlsx containing the raw inputs, formulas or executable logic (cell formulas or an attached script), computed priority values, validation checks, sensitivity calculations, flags (needs_review, escalated), and a final recommendation table with recommended action (hold, release, retest, mitigation) and estimated economic impact within decision_budget_usd; (2) qc_memo.md documenting methods, record-level citations to the embedded packet, validation checks, sensitivity notes, assumptions, any records marked needs_review (with rationale), and a compact rationale for each recommendation suitable for expert review. Use only the embedded packet for all calculations; do not use external measurements, specialized licensed software, or hidden assumptions.",
